<lb corresp="#b5"/><gap reason="ink_lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b6"/><gap reason="ink_lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt2001"/><citedRange>315-316</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in the hope of ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... at this place. (He (?)) turned back ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... now he/they now will not obtain. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (of) the Brahmins ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment">This fragment (leaf 20 of the Š-manuscript) directly follows <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht85"/>, hence its lines a1-5 must overlap with lines a5-b5 of <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht86"/>. Due to the scanty remains here – only a few akṣaras from three lines are preserved –, however, only a single overlap is to be found (<ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht86"/>: b5 and line a5 here); in line a4 and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht86"/>: b4 the texts can be merged: <hi>//// (we)ṣṣäṃ || (chanda)kanivartaṃne || ñiśmeṃ tsrorsa larepi soṃśke(nts)e ////</hi>.</note><note type="philcomment">The story is continued on <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht88"/>. The translation follows <bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt2001"/><citedRange>316</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="remarks">In one frame with <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht87b"/>.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">The restoration and correction to <hi>tso(ṅk)ai(k)</hi> "in the morning" by Sieg/Siegling in <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1953"/></bibl> (followed by Schmidt) is doubful; the visible remains of the akṣara speak in favor of <hi>tso(n)e</hi>, but such a confusoin of nasal signs is highly unlikely.</note></p>
         </div>
