               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;This fragment (leaf 20 of the Š-manuscript) directly follows [[THT 85]], hence its lines a1-5 must overlap with lines a5-b5 of [[THT 86]]. Due to the scanty remains here – only a few akṣaras from three lines are preserved –, however, only a single overlap is to be found ([[THT 86]]: b5 and line a5 here); in line a4 and [[THT 86]]: b4 the texts can be merged: &lt;i&gt;//// (we)ṣṣäṃ || (chanda)kanivartaṃne || ñiśmeṃ tsrorsa larepi soṃśke(nts)e ////&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The story is continued on [[THT 88]]. The translation follows [[Schmidt KT 2001]]: 316.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b1.&lt;/b&gt; The restoration and correction to &lt;i&gt;tso(ṅk)ai(k)&lt;/i&gt; "in the morning" by Sieg/Siegling in [[TochSprR(B) II]] (followed by Schmidt) is doubful; the visible remains of the akṣara speak in favor of &lt;i&gt;tso(n)e&lt;/i&gt;, but such a confusoin of nasal signs is highly unlikely.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
